#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:1
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr "疑難排解"

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:3
msgid ""
"This page is a collection of tips to solve problems you may encounter when "
"using Nix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:5
msgid "What to do if a binary cache is down or unreachable?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:7
msgid ""
"Pass [`--option substitute false`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-"
"ref/conf-file#conf-substitute) to Nix commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:9
msgid "How to force Nix to re-check if something exists in the binary cache?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:11
msgid ""
"Nix keeps track of what's available in binary caches so it doesn't have to "
"query them on every command. This includes negative answers, that is, if a "
"given store path cannot be substituted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:14
msgid ""
"Pass the [`--narinfo-cache-negative-ttl`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/"
"command-ref/conf-file.html#conf-narinfo-cache-negative-ttl) option to set "
"the cache timeout in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:16
msgid ""
"How to fix: `error: querying path in database: database disk image is "
"malformed`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:18
msgid "This is a [known issue](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues/1353). Try:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:21
msgid "$ sqlite3 /nix/var/nix/db/db.sqlite \"pragma integrity_check\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:25
msgid ""
"Which will print the errors in the [database](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/"
"stable/glossary#gloss-nix-database). If the errors are due to missing "
"references, the following may work:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:28
msgid ""
"$ mv /nix/var/nix/db/db.sqlite /nix/var/nix/db/db.sqlite-bkp\n"
"$ sqlite3 /nix/var/nix/db/db.sqlite-bkp \".dump\" | sqlite3 /nix/var/nix/db/"
"db.sqlite\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:33
msgid ""
"How to fix: `error: current Nix store schema is version 10, but I only "
"support 7`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:35
msgid "This is a [known issue](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues/1251)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:37
msgid ""
"It means that using a new version of Nix upgraded the SQLite schema of the "
"[database](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/glossary#gloss-nix-database), "
"and then you tried to use an older version of Nix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:39
msgid ""
"The solution is to dump the database, and use the old Nix version to re-"
"import the data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:41
msgid ""
"$ /path/to/nix/unstable/bin/nix-store --dump-db > /tmp/db.dump\n"
"$ mv /nix/var/nix/db /nix/var/nix/db.toonew\n"
"$ mkdir /nix/var/nix/db\n"
"$ nix-store --load-db < /tmp/db.dump\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:48
msgid "How to fix: `writing to file: Connection reset by peer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:50
msgid ""
"This may mean you are trying to import too large a file or directory into "
"the [Nix store](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/glossary#gloss-store), or "
"your machine is running out of resources, such as disk space or memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:52
msgid ""
"Try to reduce the size of the directory to import, or run [garbage "
"collection](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/nix-collect-"
"garbage)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:54
msgid "macOS update breaks Nix installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:56
msgid ""
"This is a [known issue](https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues/3616). The [Nix "
"installer](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/latest/installation/installing-binary) "
"modifies `/etc/zshrc`. When macOS is updated, it will typically overwrite `/"
"etc/zshrc` again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:60
msgid ""
"As a workaround, add the following code snippet to the end of `/etc/zshrc` "
"and restart the shell:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/troubleshooting.md:62
msgid ""
"if [ -e '/nix/var/nix/profiles/default/etc/profile.d/nix-daemon.sh' ]; then\n"
"  . '/nix/var/nix/profiles/default/etc/profile.d/nix-daemon.sh'\n"
"fi\n"
msgstr ""
